cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the complexity of computing equilibria in Weighted Congestion Games, which is a topic in Algorithmic Game Theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves network congestion and graph theory, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely sub-categories. The use of reductions and complexity analysis also points towards cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the study of equilibria in games involves strategic decision-making by multiple players, which falls under cs.NE (Networking and Internet Architecture).
